settings.description: When set to true, the optimizer will insert filters before a join between a nullable and non-nullable column to filter out nulls on the nullable side. This filter can add additional overhead when the file format does not fully support predicate push down.
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.filter_null_join_keys

settings.description: When set to true, the optimizer will not attempt to convert Union to Interleave
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.prefer_existing_union

settings.description: When set to true, the optimizer will push a limit operation into grouped aggregations which have no aggregate expressions, as a soft limit, emitting groups once the limit is reached, before all rows in the group are read.
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.enable_distinct_aggregation_soft_limit

settings.description: When set to true, the physical plan optimizer will prefer HashJoin over SortMergeJoin. HashJoin can work more efficiently than SortMergeJoin but consumes more memory
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.prefer_hash_join

settings.description: When set to true, the physical plan optimizer will run a top down process to reorder the join keys
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.top_down_join_key_reordering

settings.description: When set to true, the physical plan optimizer will try to add round robin repartitioning to increase parallelism to leverage more CPU cores
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.enable_round_robin_repartition

settings.description: When set to true, the source locations relative to the original SQL query (i.e. [`Span`](https://docs.rs/sqlparser/latest/sqlparser/tokenizer/struct.Span.html)) will be collected and recorded in the logical plan nodes.
settings.name: datafusion.sql_parser.collect_spans

settings.description: When sorting, below what size should data be concatenated and sorted in a single RecordBatch rather than sorted in batches and merged.
settings.name: datafusion.execution.sort_in_place_threshold_bytes

settings.description: When true, DataFusion will opportunistically remove sorts when the data is already sorted, (i.e. setting `preserve_order` to true on `RepartitionExec`  and using `SortPreservingMergeExec`) When false, DataFusion will maximize plan parallelism using `RepartitionExec` even if this requires subsequently resorting data using a `SortExec`.
settings.name: datafusion.optimizer.prefer_existing_sort

settings.description: Whether the default catalog and schema should be created automatically.
settings.name: datafusion.catalog.create_default_catalog_and_schema
